<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-30T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-30T08:00:00-05:00" n="438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">361.1121 <persName>Hrinkevich,
                                Frank</persName>/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HLW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-30T16:00:00+03:00">November
                                    30, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 30—10:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>312. Department’s 184, November 26, 2 p.m. A note has been addressed to
                            the Foreign Office requesting that the Embassy be informed of the
                            specific charges under which <persName>Hrinkevich</persName> was
                            arrested and is confined. No request is being made at this time however
                            for information regarding present status of his case since the Embassy
                            feels that the Soviet Government desires to continue its “investigation”
                            of his case until such time as he may be deported and then close the
                            matter by effecting such deportation. The Embassy fears that the lodging
                            of inquiry regarding status of the case may result in the Soviet
                            Government changing its plans and bringing him immediately to trial.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Henderson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>